# Common pip Commands

| Command                           | Description                              |
| --------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| `python -m venv env_name`         | Create a virtual environment             |
| `env_name\Scripts\activate`       | Activate on Windows                      |
| `source env_name/bin/activate`    | Activate on macOS/Linux                  |
| `deactivate`                      | Exit the virtual environment             |
| `pip install package`             | Install a package                        |
| `pip uninstall package`           | Remove a package                         |
| `pip list`                        | Display installed packages               |
| `pip show package`                | Show package details                     |
| `pip freeze`                      | Display installed packages with versions |
| `pip freeze > requirements.txt`   | Save dependencies                        |
| `pip install -r requirements.txt` | Install dependencies from a file         |
| `pip --version`                   | Display pip version                      |


